Interface Visitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TreeEvalVisitor

    public interface Visitor
    Interface for Visitor Pattern. Has visit methods for all node types.
    Author:
    Diana

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void visit(CosNode node)
      Visits a cosine node by computing the cosine of the value of the left subtree.
      void visit(DivideNode node)
      Visits a division node by dividing the value of the left subtree by the value of the right subtree.
      void visit(LogNode node)
      Visits a logarithm node by computing the logarithm to base 10 of the value of the left subtree.
      void visit(MultiplyNode node)
      Visits a multiplication node by multiplying the value of the left subtree by the value of the right subtree.
      void visit(OperandNode node)
      Visits an operand node and computes its value.
      void visit(PowerNode node)
      Visits an exponential node by raising the value of the left subtree to the power of the value of the right subtree.
      void visit(SinNode node)
      Visits a sine node by computing the sine of the value of the left subtree.
      void visit(SqrtNode node)
      Visits a square root node by computing the square root of the value of the left subtree.
      void visit(SubtractNode node)
      Visits a subtraction node by subtracting from the value of the left subtree the value of the right subtree , if the latter exists, or by computing the opposite of the value of the left subtree.
      void visit(SumNode node)
      Visits a summation node by adding the values of its subtrees.

        void visit(SqrtNode node)
        Visits a square root node by computing the square root of the value of the left subtree. Throws ZERO_LOG exception if the value is zero, or NEG_LOG exception if it is negative.
        Parameters:
        node - - a square root node.
